message.content:
The verb tenses in English language are present, past, and future tense. 

1. Present Tense: In this tense, actions or conditions described by words and phrases take effect now. Examples include "I am eating.", "She is writing a report.", "We will continue our efforts to achieve the goal."

2. Past Tense: This tense describes actions, conditions, or situations that have already occurred. Examples include "I ate breakfast.", "He read the book he had been wanting to read for a long time.", "The meeting ended after several hours.", "The storm has passed.", "She has finished her homework."

3. Future Tense: This tense describes actions, conditions, or situations that will happen in the future. Examples include "I will eat breakfast tomorrow.", "He will be attending the party next weekend.", "We will go to the movies tonight.", "The meeting is scheduled for next week.", "She will finish her homework before going to bed."
